result.execSummary:
The defendant Fady A Yousef was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Maintain full-time work, school or combination of the two.

To commit no further law violations during the period of the agreement. No violent or abusive contact with S.J.Y.  To consume no alcholic beverages or controlled substances. No entry into bars or taverns. Not to possess drug paraphernalia.

Defendant will, on or before, 3/01/17, send a written letter of apology, addressed to S.J.Y. to the DA's office. Upon approval, DA's office will forward letter to S.J.Y. Take any/all medications prescribed to the defendant by a licensed physician.  To be assessed by HELP regarding the need for counseling. If recommended, defendant shall successfully complete ATV, Anger Management or other approved course of counseling recommended by HELP. Written documentation of assessemnt, attendance and compliance must be sent to the DA's office on or before 11/01/17.    Defendant shall provide a copy of this agreement, along with the Criminal Complaint and Domestic Abuse Injunction issued 3/02/15 in case 15-CV-28, to any counselor and sign any and all releases necessary to allow the counselor (or agency) to report compliance or lack thereof to the District Attorney's Office.  Any assessments done without this agreement and the Criminal Complaint being supplied to the counselor will be considered violations of this agreement and not be accepted.  This agreement may be revoked or the defendant may have to complete a new assessment.
Pay $250 fine plus costs including domestic abuse surcharge ($619.50 - $500 cash bond = $119.50 owed). Fine/costs shall be paid to the Clerk of Courts office on or before 11/01/17.

$150 fine plus costs.  (fine/costs paid in full from cash bond posted)   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment may be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.
No contact with S.J.V., her residence or her place of employment.
Complete any counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments as appropriate resulting from the Department's COMPAS assessment.   Not to possess or use any drug paraphernalia.
